    		sessionRegistry.registerNewSession(se.getSession().getId(), null);
    	}
    }

In the above post by Paul Khodchenkov says that a `HttpSessionActivationListener` object should be stored inside a `Session`. `StandardSession` indeed has a [addSessionListener method][4], but the `StandardSession` gets created [inside of the StandardManager][5] and I&#39;m not sure how I would add a listener to those sessions.

